  <sect1 id="sec.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga">
    <title>October, 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

    <variablelist>
      <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
      <varlistentry id="vle.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga.general">
        <term>General</term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>Adjusted <xref linkend="sec.ha.installation.setup.auto"/>
                because of the renaming of the bootstrap scripts
                  <filename>sleha-init</filename>,
                  <filename>sleha-join</filename>, and
                  <filename>sleha-remove</filename> to
                  <filename>ha-cluster-init</filename>,
                  <filename>ha-cluster-join</filename>, and
                  <filename>ha-cluster-remove</filename>, respectively. Also the
                location of the log file has changed from
                  <filename>/var/log/sleha-bootstrap.log</filename> to
                  <filename>/var/log/ha-cluster-bootstrap.log</filename> (<ulink
                  url="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853772"/>).
              </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Replaced any occurrence of <command>chkconfig</command> and
                <command>rc*</command> commands with systemd equivalents (<ulink
                  url="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853533"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Introduced a consistent naming scheme for cluster names,
                node names, cluster resources, and constraints and applied it to
                the documentation. See <xref linkend="app.naming"/>.
                (Fate#314938).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Removed &hbgui; and any references pointing to it
                (Fate#312948, <ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853508"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Replaced &ais; with &corosync; (<ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853507"/>,
                  <ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853556"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Removed all occurrences of the following parameters as they
                are obsolete: <varname>default-resource-stickiness</varname>,
                  <varname>is-managed-default</varname>, and
                  <varname>default-action-timeout</varname>. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Improved the consistency of &crmshell; examples.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Adjusted changed package names throughout the whole manual
                (Fate#314807).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Removed list of resource agents from the appendix. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Moved documentation for &hageo; into a separate document
                (Fate#316121). See the new <citetitle>&hageo;
                  &geoquick;</citetitle>, available from
                &suse-onlinedoc;.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Removed <citetitle>Example of Setting Up a Simple Testing
                  Resource</citetitle> from the appendix as this can be done now
                by the &hawk; wizard. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Changed terminology for <literal>master-slave</literal>
                resources, which are now called <literal>multi-state</literal>
                resources in the upstream documentation.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Updated the screenshots.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Mentioned both <command>hb_report</command> and
                <command>crm_report</command> as command line tools for creating
                detailed cluster reports.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Numerous small fixes and additions to the manual
                based on technical feedback.</para></listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="vle.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga.concepts">
        <term><xref linkend="cha.ha.concepts"/></term>
        <!-- https://trello.com/c/pmlL29BE -->
