      <varlistentry id="vle.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga.install">
        <term><xref linkend="cha.ha.installation"/></term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <!--<listitem>
              <para>Described resource sets and templates for location 
                constraints (Fate#315158).</para>
                </listitem>-->
            <listitem>
              <para>Updated <xref linkend="sec.ha.installation.setup.manual"/>
                to reflect the software changes to the <xref
                  linkend="sec.ha.installation.setup.yast2cluster"
                  xrefstyle="select:title nopage"/>. </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>&csync; also accepts a combination of host name and IP
                address for each cluster node. See <xref
                  linkend="sec.ha.installation.setup.csync2"/>
                (Fate#314956).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><xref linkend="sec.ha.installation.autoyast"/> mentions the
                option to clone DRBD settings via &ay; (Fate#315128).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><xref linkend="pro.ha.installation.setup.ha-cluster-init"/>
                mentions <option>-t</option> option for
                <command>ha-cluster-init</command> to perform additional cluster
                configurations based on templates <ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=821123"
                  >).</ulink>
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="vle.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga.basics">
        <term><xref linkend="cha.ha.config.basics"/></term>
        <listitem>
          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                <xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.global.stonith"/> mentions
                policy change in DLM services when the global cluster option
                  <literal>stonith-enabled</literal> is set to
                  <literal>false</literal> (Fate#315195).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.tags"/> describes a new
                option to group conceptually related resources, without creating
                any colocation or ordering relationship between them
                (Fate#315101). </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para><xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.constraints.rscset"/>
                explains the concept of resource sets as an alternative format
                for defining constraints. As of &productname; 12, resource
                sets can now also be used within location constraints (whereas
                they could formerly only be used within colocation and ordering
                constraints).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Restructured <xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.maint.mode"
                /> to also cover the option of setting a whole cluster to
                maintenance mode ( <ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=829864"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Added attributes for <literal>pacemaker_remote</literal>
                service to <xref linkend="tab.ha.basics.meta"/> and added new
                section: <xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.remote"/> (<ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853535"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Added new resource agent classes to <xref
                linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.raclasses "/>:
                  <literal>systemd</literal>, <literal>service</literal>, and
                  <literal>nagios</literal> (<ulink
                  url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=853520"
                />).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
              <para>Updated <xref linkend="sec.ha.config.basics.remote.nagios"/>
                to reflect the package name changes from
                  <systemitem>nagios-plugins</systemitem> and
                  <systemitem>nagios-plugins-metadata</systemitem> to
                  <systemitem>monitoring-plugins</systemitem> and
                  <systemitem>monitoring-plugins-metadata</systemitem>,
                respectively (Fate#317780). </para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>

      <varlistentry id="vle.ha.docupdates.sle12_ga.basic.hawk">
